From: Ilies CHERGUI <ichergui@nvidia.com>
Subject: [PATCH] Fix missing <cstring> include for GCC 16

Upstream-Status: Pending

GCC 16 tightened libstdc++ header inclusions so that <cstring> is no
longer pulled in transitively through <string>, POSIX network headers,
or other standard headers.  Eleven files use std::memset / std::memcmp /
std::strncpy without including <cstring> directly, which worked by
accident on older GCC versions and breaks on GCC 16.

Signed-off-by: Ilies CHERGUI <ichergui@nvidia.com>
---
 examples/holoviz/cpp/holoviz_camera.cpp                   | 1 +
 examples/holoviz/cpp/holoviz_conditions.cpp                | 1 +
 examples/holoviz/cpp/holoviz_geometry.cpp                  | 1 +
 modules/holoinfer/src/process/transforms/generate_boxes.cpp | 1 +
 modules/holoviz/src/cuda/cuda_service.cpp                  | 1 +
 modules/holoviz/src/glfw_window.cpp                        | 1 +
 src/core/application.cpp                                   | 1 +
 src/core/cli_options.cpp                                   | 1 +
 src/core/system/gpu_resource_monitor.cpp                   | 1 +
 src/operators/ping_tensor_tx/ping_tensor_tx.cpp            | 1 +
 src/pose_tree/pose_tree_ucx_server.cpp                     | 1 +
 11 files changed, 11 insertions(+)

diff --git a/src/core/cli_options.cpp b/src/core/cli_options.cpp
--- a/src/core/cli_options.cpp
+++ b/src/core/cli_options.cpp
@@ -21,6 +21,7 @@
 #include <netdb.h>
 #include <sys/socket.h>
 #include <sys/types.h>
+#include <cstring>

 #include <string>
 #include <utility>  // std::pair
